[center][size=5][b]NIFDiff – Side-by-Side NIF Model Compare for Bethesda Games[/b][/size][/center]

[center][size=6][url=https://github.com/floyd68/NIFDiff/releases/tag/v1.1.161]v1.1.161 Release[/url][/size][/center]

[b]NIFDiff[/b] opens up to [b]8 NIF meshes at once[/b] and keeps their cameras, lighting and file selection in sync — so you can see [i]exactly[/i] how two versions of a mesh differ. A parallax/PBR mod vs. vanilla, two mods fighting over the same asset, or a before/after of your own edit.

It is a standalone, Qt-free tool: a single [b]2.3 MB executable[/b], cold start in about half a second. No installer, no runtime frameworks, no background services. Double-click a .nif and you're already comparing.

